  "prompt": "How much do partners make over a lifetime?",
  "response": "The lifetime earnings of partners, particularly in professional services such as law, accounting, or consulting, can vary widely based on several factors, including the type of firm, location, the partner's level of seniority, and individual performance. \n\nIn large law firms, for instance, equity partners often earn substantial salaries, which can range from several hundred thousand to several million dollars per year, especially in top-tier firms. Over a career that spans 20 to 40 years, this can result in earnings totaling several million to tens of millions of dollars.\n\nIn accounting firms, partners may also earn significant salaries, typically between $200,000 and $1 million annually, depending on the firm's size and the partner's role. \n\nConsulting partners in major firms can also earn large salaries, often exceeding $500,000 per year.\n\nTo summarize, lifetime earnings for partners can vary dramatically, ranging from a few million to well over $20 million or more, depending on the sector and individual circumstances.",
